Manchester United manager, Ole Gunnar Solskjaer, has revealed that midfielder, Paul Pogba would not be leaving the club in this January’s transfer window amid reports linking the 26-year-old with a move away from Old Trafford. DAILY POST had reported that Pogba has been linked with a move to Inter Milan, Real Madrid and Juventus recently. Speaking on the development after Man United’s goalless draw against Wolves in the FA Cup on Saturday, Solskjaer said as quoted by Metro UK: “No, you won’t see him go in January. “It’s always the same, speculation with players in and out. “We’re looking forward to getting Paul back on to the pitch with us.” Pogba is currently down with an ankle injury and will be out of action in the next couple of weeks.